retriesCount=0 means Nextflow's process.maxRetries path never fired.

================================================================================
3. ROOT CAUSE: maxRetries doesn't catch "Host EC2 terminated"
================================================================================

conf/aws_batch.config has process.maxRetries = 5 with no errorStrategy
override. That covers non-zero exits, OOM, timeouts — but Batch surfaces
spot reclaim as "Host EC2 terminated" with no exit code, and Nextflow
treats that as a fatal ProcessFailedException. Goes straight to
Session aborted, never increments task.attempt.

Two layers handle this case:

  a) aws.batch.maxSpotAttempts — Batch transparently re-queues the job
     before the failure surfaces to Nextflow.
  b) Per-process errorStrategy = { task.attempt <= N ? 'retry' : 'terminate' }
     — routes host-terminated through the retry counter.

Neither was set. Fix chosen: option (a), one-line global config.

