5. FSR TOOLING — TWO NEW SCRIPTS
================================================================================

I24 (Fast Snapshot Restore) draft listed enable-fsr.sh + disable-fsr.sh
as files-to-create. User got billing approval today. Wrote both.

  - infra/packer/enable-fsr.sh
      Resolves AMI from SSM /nf-reads-profiler/ami-id → root snapshot.
      Prints billing notice ($2.25/hr for 3 AZs, 1 hr minimum per AZ).
      ABORTS unless FSR_CONFIRM=yes set.
      Calls enable-fast-snapshot-restores for all 3 AZs at once.
      Polls every 30s until all reach 'enabled' (timeout default 60 min).
      Idempotent: AlreadyEnabled errors treated as success.

  - infra/packer/disable-fsr.sh
      Kill-switch: enumerates EVERY FSR pair in region (not just current
      AMI's snapshot) so a stale rolled-over AMI's snapshot can't quietly
      keep billing. No confirmation prompt — disabling is always safe.
      Verifies post-disable that no pairs remain billing.

Both pass `bash -n`, mode 755.

